{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772122224,"nonce":"8hXN1SVszroQr5GJxMyqDia6k8s=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87uNH2s","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/286","origin":"github"},"title":"Add plan-first workflow guidance to Copilot code review instructions","message":"## Summary\n\nThis repository uses a plan-first workflow: the first commit on a feature branch is often a work plan in `.agent/work-plans/PLAN_ISSUE-\u003cN\u003e.md`. Copilot code review triggers on draft PRs and currently has no guidance about this pattern, so it reviews plan files as if they were implementation.\n\n## Context\n\n- Copilot code review reads the first 4,000 characters of `.github/copilot-instructions.md` (hard limit — does not apply to Copilot Chat or coding agent)\n- The current file is ~1,200 characters, leaving room for review-specific guidance\n- Copilot code review does **not** follow `@AGENTS.md` references — review guidance must be inline in the instructions file\n- Path-specific instructions (`.github/instructions/**/*.instructions.md`) may also be useful for targeting `.agent/work-plans/` files specifically\n\n## Proposed Addition\n\nAdd a code review section near the top of `.github/copilot-instructions.md`:\n\n```markdown\n## Code Review Guidelines\n\nThis repository uses a plan-first workflow. The first commit on a feature branch\nis often a work plan in `.agent/work-plans/PLAN_ISSUE-\u003cN\u003e.md`. When reviewing:\n\n- If the PR contains only a plan file, review the plan for clarity, completeness,\n  and alignment with the principles in `docs/PRINCIPLES.md`.\n- If the PR contains implementation, review code against the plan and principles.\n- Reference `docs/PRINCIPLES.md` for workspace guiding principles.\n- Reference `docs/decisions/` for Architecture Decision Records.\n```\n\n## Additional Considerations\n\n- Could also use a path-specific instruction file (e.g., `.github/instructions/work-plans.instructions.md` with `applyTo: \".agent/work-plans/**\"`) to give Copilot plan-specific review context without using up the main file's character budget\n- The 4,000 character limit means we need to be selective about what goes in the main file — prioritize review guidance over setup instructions that only matter for Copilot Chat/coding agent\n- May want to reorder the existing file to put review-relevant content first\n\n## References\n\n- [Copilot code review docs](https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/how-tos/use-copilot-agents/request-a-code-review/use-code-review)\n- Observed during #285 — Copilot reviewed a plan-only draft PR without plan-aware context\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}